		<h2>Summary</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Requested in <span class="info">3</span>/<span class="info">26</span> calls</li>
			<li>Requested in <span class="info">3</span>/<span class="info">19</span> pure calls (<a href="../sle2009/index.html#cfp">2009</a>–<a href="../sle2013/index.html#cfp">2013</a> with the longest streak of <span class="info">2</span> years)</li>

			<li>Primary tagged in <span class="info">3</span>/<span class="info">26</span> paper bundles</li>
			<li>Primary tagged in <span class="info">3</span>/<span class="info">19</span> pure proceedings (<a href="../sle2010/index.html#lop">2010</a>–<a href="../sle2022/index.html#lop">2022</a> with the longest streak of <span class="info">1</span> years)</li>

			<li>Secondary tagged in <span class="info">14</span>/<span class="info">26</span> paper bundles</li>
			<li>Secondary tagged in <span class="info">13</span>/<span class="info">19</span> pure proceedings (<a href="../sle2008/index.html#lop">2008</a>–<a href="../sle2024/index.html#lop">2024</a> with the longest streak of <span class="info">5</span> years)</li>
			<li>Top 3 co-occurring topics:
				<ul>
					<li><a href="t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a> (<span class="info">15</span> times)</li>
					<li><a href="t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a> (<span class="info">10</span> times)</li>
					<li><a href="t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a> (<span class="info">9</span> times)</li>
				</ul>
<li>Top 3 contributors:
				<ul>
					<li><a href="../profile/DanielLaurenceMoody.html">Daniel Laurence Moody</a> (<span class="info">2</span> times)</li>
					<li><a href="../profile/EstherGuerra.html">Esther Guerra</a> (<span class="info">2</span> times)</li>
					<li><a href="../profile/JuandeLara.html">Juan de Lara</a> (<span class="info">2</span> times)</li>
				</ul>

		</ul>

<h2>List of papers (24)</h2>
<ul>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2008/index.html">SLE 2008</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2008/paper01.html">Evaluating the Visual Syntax of UML: An Analysis of the Cognitive Effectiveness of the UML Family of Diagrams</a></em> (<a href="../profile/DanielLaurenceMoody.html">Daniel Laurence Moody</a>, <a href="../profile/JosvanHillegersberg.html">Jos van Hillegersberg</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It evaluates the cognitive effectiveness/usability of UML diagram notations from a human factors perspective.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Its subject is the visual syntax/notation of UML diagrams and how visual design principles affect comprehension.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It performs an evaluation-style analysis (grounded in cognitive/notation principles) to assess UML’s visual notation quality.
">T5E</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2008s/index.html">SLE 2008 SI</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2008s/paper02.html">The “Physics” of Notations: Toward a Scientific Basis for Constructing Visual Notations in Software Engineering</a></em> (<a href="../profile/DanielLaurenceMoody.html">Daniel Laurence Moody</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The paper develops a principled design theory (principles and rationale) for constructing visual modelling notations, i.e., language design for visual syntax.
">T1A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The proposed principles aim at cognitively effective notations and improved human comprehensibility, making usability a central evaluation dimension.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It focuses on the visual (diagrammatic) representation of language constructs and how they should be visualised for effective communication.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2009/index.html">SLE 2009</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2009/paper16.html">Graphical Template Language for Transformation Synthesis</a></em> (<a href="../profile/ElīnaKalniņa.html">Elīna Kalniņa</a>, <a href="../profile/AudrisKalniņš.html">Audris Kalniņš</a>, <a href="../profile/EdgarsCelms.html">Edgars Celms</a>, <a href="../profile/AgrisŠostaks.html">Agris Šostaks</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It proposes a template language aimed at synthesizing model transformations.
">T3B</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The language is graphical, making visualization/graphical notation central to its approach.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Transformation synthesis ultimately produces mappings between source and target models.
">T4B</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2010/index.html">SLE 2010</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2010/paper22.html">Extending DMM Behavior Specifications for Visual Execution and Debugging</a></em> (<a href="../profile/NilsBandener.html">Nils Bandener</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristianSoltenborn.html">Christian Soltenborn</a>, <a href="../profile/GregorEngels.html">Gregor Engels</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The work emphasizes visual execution and debugging, i.e., visualization of runtime behavior and debugging feedback.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It builds on behavioral/executable specifications of DMM models to enable execution and debugging.
">T1C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The contribution includes tool support to execute and debug models in a visual manner.
">T4A</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2010/index.html">SLE 2010</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2010/paper23.html">Analysing the Cognitive Effectiveness of the BPMN 2.0 Visual Notation</a></em> (<a href="../profile/NicolasGenon.html">Nicolas Genon</a>, <a href="../profile/PatrickHeymans.html">Patrick Heymans</a>, <a href="../profile/DanielAmyot.html">Daniel Amyot</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The paper analyzes the cognitive effectiveness/usability of a visual notation used by BPMN 2.0.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It is directly about visualization/visual notation quality, applying principles for effective visual communication.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The analysis has implications for (re-)designing the language/notation to improve comprehensibility.
">T1A</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2011/index.html">SLE 2011</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2011/keynote1.html">Towards a One-Stop-Shop for Analysis, Transformation and Visualization of Software</a></em> (<a href="../profile/PaulKlint.html">Paul Klint</a>, <a href="../profile/BertLisser.html">Bert Lisser</a>, <a href="../profile/AtzevanderPloeg.html">Atze van der Ploeg</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It extends Rascal/IMP into a more complete workbench for analysis, transformation, and visualization.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Rascal is presented as the underlying meta-programming language used to implement these capabilities.
">T3A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The paper’s central contribution is an integrated software visualization framework layered over Rascal.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2012/index.html">SLE 2012</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2012/paper15.html">TouchRAM: A Multitouch-Enabled Tool for Aspect-Oriented Software Design</a></em> (<a href="../profile/WisamAlAbed.html">Wisam Al Abed</a>, <a href="../profile/ValentinBonnet.html">Valentin Bonnet</a>, <a href="../profile/MatthiasSchöttle.html">Matthias Schöttle</a>, <a href="../profile/EnginYıldırım.html">Engin Yıldırım</a>, <a href="../profile/OmarAlam.html">Omar Alam</a>, <a href="../profile/JörgKienzle.html">Jörg Kienzle</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The contribution is an interactive, multitouch visualization and manipulation environment for aspect-oriented design models.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Multitouch interaction is motivated by improving human usability of complex design operations and model manipulation.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It is a concrete tool implementation that supports editing/analysis workflows for aspect-oriented modeling.
">T4A</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2013/index.html">SLE 2013</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2013/paper13.html">Method and Tool Support for Classifying Software Languages with Wikipedia</a></em> (<a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a>, <a href="../profile/DominikMosen.html">Dominik Mosen</a>, <a href="../profile/AndreiVaranovich.html">Andrei Varanovich</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The main contribution is a method/tool for building a classification (taxonomy/ontology-like structure) of software languages using Wikipedia categories.
">T3E</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The tool visualizes the extracted Wikipedia category graph in a navigable, tree-like form to support exploration and understanding.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It performs analysis/mining over a large knowledge base (Wikipedia) to derive and refine language-classification structures.
">T5B</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2014/index.html">SLE 2014</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2014/keynote1.html">From Language Engineering to Viewpoint Engineering</a></em> (<a href="../profile/ColinAtkinson.html">Colin Atkinson</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The keynote’s thesis is stakeholder-facing “viewpoints” that tailor information representation and interaction to user goals and capabilities.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It calls for foundations and (implicitly) tool support for engineering viewpoints (languages + context + interaction services) efficiently.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" View-oriented engineering foregrounds presentation/visualization choices (what information is shown/elided and how it is rendered).
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL" title=" “Viewpoints” are defined as augmentations over language definitions plus contextual and interaction layers—i.e., a structured composition of concerns.
">T1D</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2014/index.html">SLE 2014</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2014/paper07.html">Evaluating the Usability of a Visual Feature Modeling Notation</a></em> (<a href="../profile/AleksandarJakšic.html">Aleksandar Jakšic</a>, <a href="../profile/RobertBFrance.html">Robert B. France</a>, <a href="../profile/PhilippeCollet.html">Philippe Collet</a>, <a href="../profile/SudiptoGhosh.html">Sudipto Ghosh</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The paper’s main contribution is a usability-focused enhancement and assessment of feature-model notations.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It introduces/uses visualization (feature diagram rendering) to improve understanding of feature models.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t2c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Feature modeling is a central technique for product lines and variability management.
">T2C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It reports an evaluation study to assess the impact of the proposed notation/tool support.
">T5E</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2014/index.html">SLE 2014</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2014/paper18.html">Streamlining Control Flow Graph Construction with DCFlow</a></em> (<a href="../profile/MarkHills.html">Mark Hills</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It introduces DCFlow, a DSL for specifying control-flow rules at the language AST level.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" DCFlow definitions are compiled into generated Rascal code that constructs CFGs.
">T4C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It is delivered as a DSL plus libraries supporting CFG extraction within a workbench setting.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Generated CFGs can be visualized, and the paper discusses visualization as a use of the produced graphs.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2015/index.html">SLE 2015</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2015/paper02.html">On integrating graphical and textual editors for a UML profile based domain specific language: an industrial experience</a></em> (<a href="../profile/SalomeMaro.html">Salome Maro</a>, <a href="../profile/JanPhilippSteghöfer.html">Jan-Philipp Steghöfer</a>, <a href="../profile/AnthonyAnjorin.html">Anthony Anjorin</a>, <a href="../profile/MatthiasTichy.html">Matthias Tichy</a>, <a href="../profile/LarsGelin.html">Lars Gelin</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The main contribution is tool/editor support that integrates graphical and textual notations for a DSL.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It directly concerns graphical notation and its synchronization with textual views (visualisation/editing).
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The case revolves around a UML-profile-based domain-specific language.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The study is positioned as an industrial experience report with an industrial partner context.
">T6B</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2015/index.html">SLE 2015</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2015/paper05.html">Example-based validation of domain-specific visual languages</a></em> (<a href="../profile/JesúsJLópezFernández.html">Jesús J. López-Fernández</a>, <a href="../profile/EstherGuerra.html">Esther Guerra</a>, <a href="../profile/JuandeLara.html">Juan de Lara</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The main focus is validating DSL definitions by checking them against example instances (testing/validation).
">T5C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It targets domain-specific languages, specifically domain-specific *visual* languages.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Because the DSLs are visual, the work directly involves graphical notation and its interpretation.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The approach is motivated by and discussed in the context of tool support for DSL engineering.
">T4A</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2016/index.html">SLE 2016</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2016/paper08.html">Execution Framework of the GEMOC Studio (Tool Demo)</a></em> (<a href="../profile/ErwanBousse.html">Erwan Bousse</a>, <a href="../profile/ThomasDegueule.html">Thomas Degueule</a>, <a href="../profile/DidierVojtisek.html">Didier Vojtisek</a>, <a href="../profile/TanjaMayerhofer.html">Tanja Mayerhofer</a>, <a href="../profile/JulienDeAntoni.html">Julien DeAntoni</a>, <a href="../profile/BenoîtCombemale.html">Benoît Combemale</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It demonstrates the GEMOC Studio’s execution framework as a meta-tool for engineering executable DSMLs.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It provides runtime services for executing DSML semantics (e.g., debugging).
">T4D</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4e.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The framework supports execution-related services such as simulation/animation of DSML models.
">T4E</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It includes graphical animation/visual feedback as part of the execution tooling.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2016/index.html">SLE 2016</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2016/paper12.html">FRaMED: Full-Fledge Role Modeling Editor (Tool Demo)</a></em> (<a href="../profile/ThomasKühn.html">Thomas Kühn</a>, <a href="../profile/KayBierzynski.html">Kay Bierzynski</a>, <a href="../profile/SebastianRichly.html">Sebastian Richly</a>, <a href="../profile/UweAßmann.html">Uwe Aßmann</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It presents an editor/tool for role modeling—i.e., language workbench-style tooling for a modeling language.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Role modeling is supported through a graphical editor/notation, emphasizing visualization.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The tool targets a specific modeling language (role modeling) in a DSL/DSML setting.
">T3C</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2016/index.html">SLE 2016</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2016/paper23.html">Xdiagram: A Declarative Textual DSL for Describing Diagram Editors (Tool Demo)</a></em> (<a href="../profile/AndreLuísdeMedeirosSantos.html">Andre Luís de Medeiros Santos</a>, <a href="../profile/EduardoGomes.html">Eduardo Gomes</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM" title=" Xdiagram is a DSL for specifying diagram editors for DSMLs.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It is meant to generate/support tooling (diagram editors), i.e., meta-tooling for language workbenches.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Its purpose is to define and realize graphical syntax/editors, directly tied to visualization.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It supports language design by enabling definition of concrete (diagrammatic) notations.
">T1A</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2017/index.html">SLE 2017</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2017/paper09.html">Concrete syntax: a multi-paradigm modelling approach</a></em> (<a href="../profile/YentlVanTendeloo.html">Yentl Van Tendeloo</a>, <a href="../profile/SimonVanMierlo.html">Simon Van Mierlo</a>, <a href="../profile/BartMeyers.html">Bart Meyers</a>, <a href="../profile/HansVangheluwe.html">Hans Vangheluwe</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It proposes a multi-paradigm approach to defining concrete syntax, i.e., language design of notations.
">T1A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The work is motivated by domain-specific modeling languages and how their syntax is defined.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Concrete syntax work typically spans visual/textual notations, and the paper explicitly targets multi-paradigm (incl. visual) syntax.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It emphasizes coordinating multiple syntactic paradigms for the same language, requiring integration between notation forms.
">T1D</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2019/index.html">SLE 2019</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2019/paper11.html">Domain-specific model differencing in visual concrete syntax</a></em> (<a href="../profile/ManouchehrZadahmad.html">Manouchehr Zadahmad</a>, <a href="../profile/EugeneSyriani.html">Eugene Syriani</a>, <a href="../profile/OmarAlam.html">Omar Alam</a>, <a href="../profile/EstherGuerra.html">Esther Guerra</a>, <a href="../profile/JuandeLara.html">Juan de Lara</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The paper mainly targets domain-specific languages or modeling languages, including their design or use.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It focuses on visualization or graphical notation/editing as a substantial aspect of the work.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2022/index.html">SLE 2022</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2022/paper06.html">Workbench for Creating Block-Based Environments</a></em> (<a href="../profile/MauricioVeranoMerino.html">Mauricio Verano Merino</a>, <a href="../profile/KoenvanWijk.html">Koen van Wijk</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It presents a workbench to build block-based programming environments.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Block-based environments are visual languages and the work targets their visual tooling.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The goal is to support usable, end-user-friendly editing and interaction.
">T5H</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2022/index.html">SLE 2022</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2022/paper13.html">Property Probes: Source Code Based Exploration of Program Analysis Results</a></em> (<a href="../profile/AntonRisbergAlaküla.html">Anton Risberg Alaküla</a>, <a href="../profile/GörelHedin.html">Görel Hedin</a>, <a href="../profile/NiklasFors.html">Niklas Fors</a>, <a href="../profile/AdrianPop.html">Adrian Pop</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagM" title=" Property probes provide interactive visualization/exploration of program analysis results in source code.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It delivers tooling support to inspect and navigate analysis outcomes.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The interface is designed to support developer comprehension and interactive investigation.
">T5H</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2023/index.html">SLE 2023</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2023/paper14.html">Enabling Blended Modelling of Timing and Variability in EAST-ADL</a></em> (<a href="../profile/MuhammadWaseemAnwar.html">Muhammad Waseem Anwar</a>, <a href="../profile/FedericoCiccozzi.html">Federico Ciccozzi</a>, <a href="../profile/AlessioBucaioni.html">Alessio Bucaioni</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The work extends and supports the EAST-ADL domain-specific modelling language with blended modelling facilities.
">T3C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t2c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" A major concern is variability modelling, which aligns with product-line style variability management.
">T2C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t6f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" EAST-ADL targets automotive embedded systems, placing the contribution in a CPS/IoT domain context.
">T6F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Blended modelling involves multiple concrete syntaxes (often including graphical views), making visual interaction a secondary concern.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2023/index.html">SLE 2023</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2023/paper17.html">A Low-Code Platform for Systematic Component-Oriented Language Composition</a></em> (<a href="../profile/JérômePfeiffer.html">Jérôme Pfeiffer</a>, <a href="../profile/AndreasWortmann.html">Andreas Wortmann</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The main contribution is a low-code platform (tool) that supports systematic component-oriented language composition.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The platform operationalizes language composition mechanisms by coordinating multiple language constituents (syntax and semantics).
">T1D</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The approach relies on a graphical, web-based interface typical of visualization-oriented tooling.
">T4F</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2024/index.html">SLE 2024</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2024/paper02.html">Aconite: Towards Generating Sirius-Based Graphical Editors from Annotated Metamodels</a></em> (<a href="../profile/NathanRichardson.html">Nathan Richardson</a>, <a href="../profile/DimitriosSKolovos.html">Dimitrios S. Kolovos</a>, <a href="../profile/AntonioGarcíaDomínguez.html">Antonio García-Domínguez</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It presents tooling to generate Sirius-based graphical editors automatically from annotated metamodels.
">T4A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Editor generation is a vertical/generative process that derives concrete tooling artifacts from language models.
">T4C</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The generated artifacts are graphical/diagrammatic editors, directly targeting visualization of DSL instances.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The approach targets metamodel-based DSLs whose editors are derived from their language definitions.
">T3C</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2024/index.html">SLE 2024</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2024/paper09.html">The Linguistic Theory behind Blockly Languages</a></em> (<a href="../profile/FriedrichSteimann.html">Friedrich Steimann</a>, <a href="../profile/RobinStunic.html">Robin Stunic</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM" title=" It develops a principled account of how Blockly-style block languages are designed and structured.
">T1A</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Blockly’s block-based notation is a visual syntax whose structure and affordances are a primary focus.
">T4F</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The motivation is grounded in learnability/usability for novices and end-user programmers.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL" title=" Blockly configurations are effectively DSLs whose syntax is instantiated from a language definition.
">T3C</span></a></li></ul>
